        <h2><b>Catherine Bisset</b></h2>

        <p>
          Catherine Bisset is a Scottish-based actor and writer of Jamaican and English Heritage. She only started acting in her late 40s, but after joining Edinburgh Acting School, she has performed in a number of plays, often cast against type, playing Macbeth, Mary Queen of Scots, Felicity Cunningham in <i>The Real Inspector Hound</i>, and the Magistrate in <i>Lysistrata</i>. She was the lead artist for a filmed verbatim project funded by Stellar Quines, and has recently written and performed her first solo play <i>Placeholder</i>, which came runner up in the Production of the Year category in the Framework Theatre Awards for emerging artists.
        </p>
