        <h2><b>Conor O'Dwyer</b></h2>

        <p>
          Conor O’Dwyer is an Irish actor from Galway. He moved to Edinburgh in January 2021, looking for a change of scene in the lockdown. Conor is now a 2022 graduate of the BA Acting at the MGA Academy of Performing Arts in Edinburgh. His graduate shows included <i>The Comedy of Errors</i> directed by Paul Brotherston and <i>The Sweet Science of Bruising</i> directed by Molly Innes. <i>The Masks of Oscar Wilde</i> is Conor’s professional theatrical debut.
        </p>

        <p>
          Conor is also a graduate of Bow Street Academy for Screen Acting in Dublin, graduating in 2017. His screen work includes <i>Dublin Murders</i> and <i>The Wake</i>. Conor started creating his own comedy sketches on YouTube during the lockdown, and they have now amassed a viewership of over 400,000. Conor is also an avid swimmer, reader, and coffee drinker. Guilty pleasures include Pokémon and bingeing YouTube videos.
