        <h2>Written by <b>Shaul Ezer</b></h2>
        <p>
          Shaul is a playwright and novelist living in Montreal, Canada. His works include a trilogy of plays about each city in Canada in which he lived: <i>The Matchmaker of Montreal</i>, a romantic comedy set in Montreal, which premiered in 2013 at The Firehall Arts Centre in Vancouver; <i>The Concierge of Vancouver</i>, a comedy about the Vancouver housing crisis which opened October 6, 2016 at Studio 1398 in Vancouver; and the third part of the trilogy which is being written and will be set in Toronto.
        </p>

        <p>
          Shaul's other works include <i>The Masks of Oscar Wilde</i>, a play about Wilde’s life, which premiered in Vancouver in 2014, <i>The Real William Shakespeare, as Told by Christopher Marlowe</i>, to be premiered at EdFringe in 2023, and <i>To Hell with PC</i>, a satire of political correctness (still in development). His plays are produced by his Montreal-based company Matchmaker Productions.
        </p>

        <p>
          Shaul has written novels including <i>Moses and the Nubian Princess</i>, a biblical novel about the Israelite leader and the black woman he married, and the sequel <i>Joshua and the Conquest of Jericho</i>. He's written three children travelogues about the adventures of his grandchildren with Baby Cloud, a cloud who takes them flying around their neighbourhood. He's also written a law book <i>International Exporting Agreements</i>, published in 1985 by LexisNexis, New York.
        </p>
